&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Practice Educator Post Registration Education: Recruitment &amp; Retention&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£38,890 – £44,503 Per Annum Pro rata&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;30 Hours per week &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;About us&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at George Eliot our vision to &lt;em&gt;‘&lt;strong&gt;excel at patient care’&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; takes centre stage. An ever evolving clinically-led acute service provider we are on a journey to continually provide high quality, safe and responsive services delivered by inspiring, friendly and compassionate staff who share our corporate values which underpin everything we do. Our values are not just words on a piece of paper, they bond us together, reflect our ambition and shape who we are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;ffective Open Communication&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;e&lt;strong&gt;x&lt;/strong&gt;cellence and safety in everything we do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C&lt;/strong&gt;hallenge but support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;xpect respect and dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;L&lt;/strong&gt;ocal health that inspires confidence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Role&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for someone that has the vision and enthusiasm to work on the post registration agenda, someone who can take the lead on recruitment and retention of the nursing workforce, supporting both local and international nurse recruitment and workforce retention initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be instrumental in ensuring the clinical workforce has the knowledge, skills and ability to provide a high standard of patient care. Identifying talent pipe lines and supporting effective use of the CPD resource, to the benefit of individuals in their career development and the organisation in relation to service developments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work with the Practice Education team, alongside colleagues responsible for the Pre- registration agendas and Health Care Assistant development. You will need to work independently and make key decisions in the interests of others prioritising your work load. There is a requirement to be clinically current and have a keen interest in the development and support of the registered clinical workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent communication skills are essential. Experience of supervising and assessing nurses in practice would be required along with an understanding of the process to gaining NMC status. Experience of recruitment using the TRAC process would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Benefits &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our benefits include but are not limited to: On-site nursery, 27 days minimum annual leave plus 8 bank holidays, cycle to work scheme, flexible working, on-site discounted gym, extensive in-house course learning directory, buying and selling of annual leave, subsidised restaurant, tranquillity garden and generous subsidised on-site parking.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 22 – November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: 08 December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post may close early due to high numbers of applications &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;So you are advised to apply promptly.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All correspondence for this vacancy will be sent by email; please check your account regularly including your Junk and SPAM areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;A great and friendly place to work, so bring your passion, commitment and expertise &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;and enjoy the opportunities to make a difference every day. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
